reviewText:
To be very clear - you might not like the game.

However, I spent ¬£0.49 on it, and I've had my monies worth after 20 minutes. I didn't expect it to be good, and it is not great, but it is good (for me). It has been witty, funny, clever, and made me really smile at moments.

It has a jerky type of movement that reminds me of the old games before smooth animation was invented. However, it feels responsive, and the character moves where I tell it. So the jerky movement is a great recreation, spot-on in fact. The artwork is a mix of acceptable bad mixed with some pretty good art for a top-down game. The sound effects ... or rather the voices and vocal recordings are exceptional. There is a lot of speech involved which adds a lot to the simple experience.

What attracted me to the game was the price of course. However, I thought the ranting discussion threads created by people with nothing better to do than find an object to attack (love the internet!!), were too drama-like to ignore.

I bought the game to see what the fuss was about (bearing in mind most of the ranters might not have actually played the game). And they were wrong. It is not a bad game. It is not a great game. A great game would be the original GTA, Or other top-downs like Prison Architect. However, is it worth supporting an indie with ¬£0.49 of my money? Yeah, I am happy. If the ranters keep publicising the game I reckon the devs will be very happy too!!

---

TL;DR --- To sum up, the game costs ¬£0.49 and ¬£0.49 buys me 25% of a tub of cherries from Waitrose. I can eat 25% of the tub in 5 mins. This game has been played 20 minutes and after this review I am going back to it. After a full tub of cherries at ¬£2 and 20 minutes later - I get rampant farts and stomach ache. Take my advice - buy the game (if you like different styles of games) and do not eat a full tub of cherries in 20 minutes!!

reviewText:
OverviewNotGTAV is indeed, not GTA V. This short game was made in the course of a week by British developer team NotGames and is basically a satirical comedy game that pokes hints at GTA, but that adds it's own elements of comic relief. Gameplay wise, this is nothing more than a game of snake.

The Pros: It's fun(ny) - While the game of snake can only get so good, due to the nature of this game, it is quite fun to play. This mainly consists of the mouth-made soundtrack of the game and the accent-driven voice-overs you can hear when nearing your targets. Every time you play it, you listen more closely and discover a new joke.
Charity - Besides the fact that this game comes at a very low price, all the profits go to charity, so you know that your money was well spent for this funny little time waster.
Difficulty Setting - The game offers you several challenges with the different difficulty levels, which may actually prove frustrating and should be attempted only by the bravest of casual gamers. These modify things such as movement speed, time limits, and the use of checkpoints.
The.. uh.. Graphics? - Normally bad graphics and production value of a game should be treated as a con, but in this case it is a feature. The hand-made textures, choppy or nonexistent animations and mouth made sound effects are what makes this game even more enjoyable and truly brings the parody effect to life.
Steam Features - Games with good steam integration always get bonus points from me. I'm pleased to see Trading Cards from a game such as this, as well as a decently long list of fun and relatively easy achievements. Other features like Steam Cloud are not applicable here, as the game is short and does not have progression that needs to be saved.
The Cons: Short - Understandable for a game made for amusement and in a weeks time, so don't expect any length from this. The game can be beaten in about 15-20 minutes once you get the hang of it, and it has three stages with 6 levels each, the last one having two variations.
No Level Selection - The game does not have a level selection menu, so if you enjoyed, say, the Lidl level, you will have to replay the camping one first. This would have been an easy to add feature that I'm disappointed is missing.
Horrible Menus - The game does have mouse controls, but no cursor, and the menus are poorly drawn and are controlled via hotkeys. I presume they made it on purpose, but a few extra options and the ability to use a mouse would have been nice.
ConclusionThis game is for people who want to support charity and have a chuckle for a few minutes, as its replay value does not equate for more than two or three hours tops. Buy it if you like Snake and are bored out of your mind.

reviewText:
Best. 51 minutes. Ever.

Very rarely am I compelled enough these days to buy a game as soon as I see it (even though it was only 50p so it doesn‚Äôt really count) but even rarer do I actually buy a game then boot it up as soon as I can. I‚Äôm that person that buys games 3 years late when they are deduced to 75% because everyone already bloody has it, takes another 3 years to actually play it and then wonders why no one else is hyping with me when I finally get around to seeing why it was a popular game in the first place. In all honesty, it‚Äôs a stupid routine I have. My point being for once I actually outright bought and played a game out of curiosity.

I am British, so the humour of this was what appealed to me most. That and the fact I have been craving a snake-like game recently. It looked pretty funny and I didn‚Äôt want to be starting any games that would take me too long to finish, so this was perfect for the mood I was in.
I think when it comes to the humour of this game, only British people are going to find it funny. There is a very drastic difference between English and American humour in my opinion. A lot of the references in this game are kind of ‚Äúinside jokes‚Äù amongst British culture. AKA, if you are not from the UK, you might not find this funny at all.

This game is extremely poor quality and I love it. It looks like it was drawn by a child, the voices and sound effects are terribly stereotypical and the game is just generally ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. In the best way!
It‚Äôs a short game, I completed it fairly quickly. According to Steam I spent 51 minutes on this game. I completed the game and got 56% of the achievements. So this isn‚Äôt something you are going to be sinking a lot of time into.

I do expect I will be going back to this to try and collect the achievements (of which I will likely update this review if I do).

I personally think it was a fun little quirky game that really shows what sarcastic ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• us British people are. It makes me proud to me British (I think).


TL;DR : NotGTAV is a quirky, sarky little game that I think British people will enjoy. It‚Äôs extremely poorly done in the best of ways. It‚Äôs a light little snake-like game that I thought was a bit of fun. I like the general concept of it. It‚Äôs short but sweet, buy it if you are looking to kill an hour.

reviewText:
Brief & whimsical // Recommended for brief jaunts of a decidedly silly nature
+ Quirky, endearing soundtrack; good for keeping a goofy smile on the player's face as they play through the abstract experience
+ Audio design, both sounds and voiceovers, is infectiously charming and funny
+ Hand-drawn visuals fit the rest of the game like a glove; adds immesurably to the droll atmosphere
+ Gameplay boils down to obstacle avoidance, timing, and tail management; mechanics are simple, but the difficulty increases gradually, just enough to keep one on one's toes
+ Sale proceeds go to charity

- Extremely short; a full playthrough can be accomplished, quite easily, in well under an hour
- No resolution options, and the default resolution is frustratingly small
- Save for trading cards and achievements, there is precious little in the way of replay value

reviewText:
NotGTAV is pretty much Snake if made by a team with no talent but decent humor. If you are not familiar with Snake well the point of it is to collect pieces to grow larger and avoid crashing into your own body. In this game your body is made of hobos, animals and other odd things. In levels you either walk around, push a shopping cart around or drive a car but the controls are exactly the same so it doesn't really matter. Thrown about the levels are obstacles to avoid and objects to collect or run over. And that's pretty much all you will be doing throughout the game though with different environments and jokes. The humor is the best part of this game though it is very hit or miss.

Controls are barely passable but the animations and the sense of speed make telling when to turn difficult. You may get used to the rhythm but  overtime you start moving faster causing you to lose your flow and hope that you have gotten used enough to the awful moving animation to survive. Levels also become harder to navigate as the game goes on but it does it in a very cheap fashion. All the while the most terrible music and sound effects I ever had the displeasure of hearing played. Most of the sound effects are made via mouth and the voice acting is just as bad. It was probably meant to be humorous but it is extremely irritating in my opinion.

In a few sections you can choose whether to go sneaky or brutal but going sneaky is a massive pain due to how the level is designed to be so small and touching a person kills you. Going brutal is more tolerable but it adds a bunch of people to run over and you must get every single one of them. That sounds a lot more fun on paper than it actually is due to the level design meant to annoy you and subpar controls. Even the options menu is annoying to read with how the font is written. Naming this game ‚ÄúNotGTAV‚Äù while not really having anything in common with GTA or even reference it all that much is a scumbag way to promote your terrible game. It wouldn't be a big deal if they made a fun game but this is quite possibly the worst game I have played on Steam and feels like a cash grab.

Yes, I am aware they stated 100% of the profits will be given to charity and if that's the case simply cut out the middle man and donate if you are inclined. This is an awful game and promoting this type of cash grab with a purchase is not something I would recommend to anybody. This is a sentence from their Steam page ‚ÄúBy buying this game you can help us pay something back.‚Äù. And to that I say, well either start a fundraiser of some type or make a decent game instead of trying to pity people into buying rubbish. I know this may seem harsh to a lot of people but this is a really bad game that I probably wouldn't even recommend if it was free.

The trailers are probably the most entertaining part of this product and even then most of the footage is from Grand Theft Auto V. When low brow humor and terrible animations are your only talents you would be better off making a Youtube channel instead of utterly failing at making a Snake clone. Moving on from that, this is really a title with a very certain type of audience. That would be the people that are curious about this title and are willing to risk it for the small price or those that want to prove how edgy they are. If you are looking for a fun game or a decent clone of Snake you won't find anything to enjoy here. If you are looking for dark humor then you might find it here but would still have to play through the game to reach the jokes. Overall I can't recommend this to anybody.

reviewText: I rolled my eyes when I first saw this game.  At first I found it annoying that somebody was trying to make money by dropping the name of a AAA title into their game.  Though I was much less annoyed when I discovered that they are giving the majority of the money that they make to a charity.  So this will be a short and sweet review.  It's snake, you know that old arcade game?  These days people can play it on their calculator, but this version has a bit more character, and if you have actually played GTA V you will probably enjoy it a bit more.  There are 3 different areas, each one includes a starting area and then a heist afterwards, for a total of 6 levels.  I'd say the funniest thing about this game is that all of the graphics are hand drawn with either crayon or colored pencil and all of the sound affects are done by voice, which is entertaining.  The disclaimer at the beginning was enough to get me laughing.  Overall its a short game, and it's at least worth a few laughs, so make sure you have a sense of humor coming into it.

reviewText:
This game is amazing!
Truely a work of art redefining the genre of snake games by adding the GTA V element to it, without being GTA V!

If you purchase this game you will be stunned by the artwork, you can't find anything like this in just any ordinary game. It's almost as if it were drawn in MS Paint, but it wasnt! As an artist myself, I have been trying to perfect this brilliant eyepopping art style for the past 4 years and haven't come close!

The music and sound effects are unreal. If you love British voices then you'll love this game! All the vehicles, NPCs, and animals are fully voiced! The sound effects for killing people, picking up items, everything is just so well done. My favorite would have to be the different radio stations. I wish there was a download for them so I could listen to them while driving around town. As a musician myself, I haven't heard music performed/recorded better then in this game!

The gameplay is incredibly challenging. I often found myself struggling with levels and frustrated more then Dark Souls, but would feel better achieved from overcoming the challenge then from any game. This game had me on the edge of my seat throughout the whole thing! I would put the gameplay here well over GTA V's gameplay style. They are differnt of course because this is not GTA V. As a gameplay designer myself, I have been struggling to work hard on how to create the best user experience in a game and I think that NotGTAV has just given me the breakthrough idea of a lifetime!

I cannot wait for NotGTAVI to release. Perhaps we could get a prequel, NotGTAIV ? I would love that! As a NotGTA myself, I have been working hard to release a new version, but I know that these dev's can do it.

11/10 - Would have payed 60$ for this instead of GTAV.

reviewText: Short, simple game. Horrible AI in the heist levels. Repetitive dialogue. They're funny the first time, hearing it afterwards is just irritating. The game is basically glorified snake with an attempt to parody GTA V, which, seeing as the game takes place in the UK, doesn't make very much sense. It probably makes more sense if you view the name NotGTAV as a marketing tactic that piggybacks on another popular game. The difficulty levels are just the game sped up, there's nothing else unique about them to warrant a replay other than the sake of completion. On the plus side, the soundtrack is decent and complements the hand-drawn style well enough. It's great that all the proceeds from sales are going to charity, but that's one of only a few redeeming qualities this game has. It's almost like an excuse for making a half-‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• game. That should not be the sole reason for you to buy it, though. You can always donate to charity on your own volition.\n\nIs it worth the 74 cents I spent during the sale? Well, I enjoyed it more than a $1 can of soda, so yes. If you want a few laughs, buy it when it's less than a dollar, then sell the trading cards for most of your money back. Otherwise, wouldn't recommend.

reviewText:
Imagine playing snake.

Imagine playing snake on hand-drawn refrigerator pictures.

Imagine playing snake on hand-drawn refrigerator pictures while mumbled voiceovers describe British culture references to you.

This game is the kind of flash game that would be on the internet 6 years ago as a free download, as a small, forgettable project someone made before working on something they deemed more valuable of their time. Worth 3 dollars? No. Worth 75 cents? No. This game is like a novelty store gag, and like one, will make you question what you're doing with your time and money. Just don't get it.

reviewText:
NotGTA is perhaps the best game ever.

It follows three characters Dyfed (Dyffd??), Darren and David Cameron.

Dyfed, a lonely choir singer from the Welsh valleys must set forth on a quest to reunite himself with his lost love; bessy the sheep. Being something of a romantic comedy film this will leave you gasping in amazement, and crying in tears, not unlike at the end of Toy Story 3. Its a story will all the Romantic volume of the novel 'Fifthy Shades of Grey' and twice the adult scenes. As a romatic story, this game has won a nobel prize.

The second chapter follows Darren: an underdog from the slums of the Swindon. Guide him through the ranks as this man pushes past social and economic bounderies to change the face of the UK. All the while Battling against his alcohol addicted father. if the love story of Dyfed the Welshman didn't bring you to tears, then this will too; and make you feel generally hyped.

And finally: follow the rise of David cameron as he plots he way to teh top of the British political system, make engaging morality based decisions similar to Mass Effect and Half Life 3. In this Gameofthronesish setting, play politics against the great names of the Political World: George Bush, Barack Obama and Lindsay Lohan.

106/10
Game of the year
5 Stars.

Method:

Blending in the flour: Put the flour and a pinch of salt into a large mixing bowl and make a well in the centre. Crack the eggs into the middle, then pour in about 50ml milk and 1 tbsp oil. Start whisking from the centre, gradually drawing the flour into the eggs, milk and oil. Once all the flour is incorporated, beat until you have a smooth, thick paste. Add a little more milk if it is too stiff to beat.
Finishing the batter: Add a good splash of milk and whisk to loosen the thick batter. While still whisking, pour in a steady stream of the remaining milk. Continue pouring and whisking until you have a batter that is the consistency of slightly thick single cream. Traditionally, people would say to now leave the batter for 30 mins, to allow the starch in the flour to swell, but there‚Äôs no need.
Getting the right thickness: Heat the pan over a moderate heat, then wipe it with oiled kitchen paper. Ladle some batter into the pan, tilting the pan to move the mixture around for a thin and even layer. Quickly pour any excess batter into a jug, return the pan to the heat, then leave to cook, undisturbed, for about 30 secs. Pour the excess batter from the jug back into the mixing bowl. If the pan is the right temperature, the pancake should turn golden underneath after about 30 secs and will be ready to turn.
Flipping pancakes: Hold the pan handle, ease a fish slice under the pancake, then quickly lift and flip it over. Make sure the pancake is lying flat against base of the pan with no folds, then cook for another 30 secs before turning out onto a warm plate. Continue with the rest of the batter, serving them as you cook or stack onto a plate. You can freeze the pancakes for 1 month, wrapped in cling film or make them up to a day ahead.

reviewText:
When I started up the game, I was greeted with a message. This message was displayed on-screen in white letters scrolling quickly down a black background and being read at a fast pace ‚Äì how could this not be funny? What it explains is what the game is, why they made it and, most of all, politics. Yes, politics. Because this game was made for charity, and all proceeds of this game go to charity. There‚Äôs even a joke in this start-up speech about how, if you pirate the game, you‚Äôre so morally low that you should have Somali pirates come into your house and cut your gaming fingers off to teach you the real definition of the word ‚Äòpiracy‚Äô. The narrator then goes on to attack David Cameron for letting bankers off the hook whilst not caring about charities like the one this game is funding. This made me fall in love with the game before I even got any gameplay.
After the game actually started, I was treated to several achievements for just browsing the options menu and altering some values. As soon as that was over, I went into the main game and played as the first playable character, Dafydd. His story is set in Wales. There are two other playable characters in the game too, but these only come into play later on. These are Darren, who is supposed to be a ‚Äòchav‚Äô from Swindon and, of course, David Cameron. All of these characters are supposed to be funny, and to me they are hilarious. From Kenneth‚Äôs accent (Kenneth is the manager of Lidl Swindon and the ‚Äòenemy‚Äô (if you will) of Darren) to the way in which the David Cameron character says lines which we all know the real David Cameron does off of the camera, this game‚Äôs attempt at poor writing and bad jokes is what, in a way, makes the writing and jokes all the more fun!
Now, of course, one of the big things in Grand Theft Auto V is Heists. And I know that you‚Äôre asking ‚ÄúAre there heists in NotGTAV?‚Äù The answer: yes. But they‚Äôre not quite what you‚Äôd imagine. To be honest, I‚Äôve only played the first two at this point and I don‚Äôt know if there‚Äôs a David Cameron heist (but I assume that there is and that it is entertaining), but what I got is this ‚Äì you do something stereotypical of the character that you are playing as and, like in GTAV, there are two paths that you can take: the loud or the quiet. And, in short, they do what the GTAV ones do ‚Äì the loud one makes you massacre everybody, the quiet one makes you become a Sam Fisher wannabe. Both are equally entertaining, and both are worth replaying the heist to see pan out.
At the end of the day, NotGTAV is a parodic game, made to spoof the real Grand Theft Auto V poorly and also made to entertain you. Now, does it do that? Most certainly! In fact, since the game does this so well, I love it all the more! I may have only played a little over an hour of it as of me writing this, but I still enjoyed it massively ‚Äì and would recommend it to anybody who has seen it anywhere before. Sure the graphics are shoddy and the sounds were all made by people making noises into microphones, but that‚Äôs what I love about it. This game does exactly what it is meant to do, and is deliberately poor in audio and video whereas most AAA games today do that by accident.

reviewText:
This is definitely NOT GTAV.

What it IS, though, is awesome. This is essentially a clone of the old flip-phone game Snake, with a GTA-esque twist. The gameplay is simple, using just a couple of buttons to turn left or right and try not to run into the stuff you're not supposed to run into, and run into the stuff you're supposed to run into.

It's the kind of game that you can play for three hours and have fun the whole time, or play for five minutes and be satisfied. The art style isn't that great, basically it looks like someone drew it on a piece of notebook paper, which fits with the Not GTAV" theme as if someone was doodling this game in class at school.

It's hard to write an in-depth review of a game that has no depth. If it looks fun
recommended: but if you don't like Snake or GTAV
hoursPlayed: don't get it. It's as simple as that. I had fun with it
voteText:
and if you can't afford GTAV then this is the next best thing.

reviewText:
I have spent 3.8 hours of my life so far playing this game, and holy ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•... it blew me away.
It is impressive running on my GTX Titan Z and I am shocked as I did not expect this. I get a decent 697 frames anyway.

Pros:
Really decent voice actors

Really intensive in depth music

Fantasic Storyline

Profits go to charity

Graphically detailed and impressive artwork (Reason why im shocked that it could run on my GTX Titan Z)

Very cool achievements

There is trading cards

Microphone quality is astounding

Fantastic location to base the game in

Voice actors are very relaxing to listen to

Cons:
Nigel Farage is not in this game

You have to hear a really detailed impersonation of david cameron & see graphically detailed artwork of david cameron to complete the game

The graphics are very intensive meaning that this game could be quite hard to run for some people

The music can get repetative which is a shame because it is very beautifully made and I know the music artists are capable of crafting more fantastic background music.


Summary:

It is a fantasic game. Ignore the minoritys, this game is worth your time as it really is an action packed achievements.
I recommend you wear headphones to really feel like you are in the game and enjoy the fantastic music.
I recommend competing with your friends to see who can get acheivements and badges first.

reviewText:
One of the best Indie titles I've played in a while. It really captures the essence of GTA V, but it isn't GTA V. If you are looking for a great, cheap alternative to GTA V without multiplayer, and real-time action combat. Then Not GTAV is for you.
The story of Not GTAV is amazing. You are constantly in the action, running ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• over with a tractor, cart, or car. I really feel like I am a part of the story and I become deeply emmerssed in the gameplay. Whenever I am looking to unwind and have some fun, I always find myself gravitating towards this amazing title.
The gameplay is smooth and highly optimized for PC. The controls work perfectly with no delay at all. The voice acting and music is what really takes the cake though, the time that went in to composing and performing the music in this masterpiece is astonishing.
Overall I rate this game an 8/10.
9/10 for gameplay
7/10 for story

reviewText:
One of the best Indie titles I've played in a while. It really captures the essence of GTA V, but it isn't GTA V. If you are looking for a great, cheap alternative to GTA V without multiplayer, and real-time action combat. Then Not GTAV is for you.
The story of Not GTAV is amazing. You are constantly in the action, running ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• over with a tractor, cart, or car. I really feel like I am a part of the story and I become deeply emmerssed in the gameplay. Whenever I am looking to unwind and have some fun, I always find myself gravitating towards this amazing title.
The gameplay is smooth and highly optimized for PC. The controls work perfectly with no delay at all. The voice acting and music is what really takes the cake though, the time that went in to composing and performing the music in this masterpiece is astonishing.
Overall I rate this game an 8/10.
9/10 for gameplay
7/10 for story

I highly reccomend this game... not for the replayablility aspect of it but the pure comedic aspect and the fact that all proceeds go to a charity, Peer Productions based in the UK. I only wish I hadn't of bought this when it was on sale but maybe my gameplays can persuade others to help support NotGames and PeerProductions.

The Positives
Hand drawn graphics
The graphics are handdrawn which adds to the creativity of the game in my opinion.

Acapella Sound Effects
Along with hand drawn graphics are the home recorded sound effects.

Hilarious dialog
The dialog of this game is quite simply hilarious. This again adds to the creativity aspect

Negatives
Control Response
Sometimes it feels like the controls don't respond in time and I end up crashing. I was starting to wonder if the David Cameron level was mean to never end due to the paranoid delusion that the game was engineered to allow run cameron's car into ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• thus killing him.

reviewText:
The positive
- All proceeds go to charity.
- There are humerous moments (the missions parody the actual gta v by placing emphasis on smaller things, like stealing soap, or items, etc).
- Nice elements of parody. I especially enjoyed the radio.

The negative:
- The format of the game is like that snake game where you have to eat things to get bigger. (It wouldn't have been a problem if the maps didn't cause the difficulty to spike to painful levels. )
- Sometimes the controls don't respond well.

Overall: This was pretty fun at first, and even if it did get painful during some levels, it was mostly enjoyable. If the NotCOD is serious, I really think that it should have a more open area, and the eating snake game aspect is removed.

I highly reccomend this game... not for the replayablility aspect of it but the pure comedic aspect and the fact that all proceeds go to a charity, Peer Productions based in the UK. I only wish I hadn't of bought this when it was on sale but maybe my gameplays can persuade others to help support NotGames and PeerProductions.

The Positives
Hand drawn graphics
The graphics are handdrawn which adds to the creativity of the game in my opinion.

Acapella Sound Effects
Along with hand drawn graphics are the home recorded sound effects.

Hilarious dialog
The dialog of this game is quite simply hilarious. This again adds to the creativity aspect

Negatives
Control Response
Sometimes it feels like the controls don't respond in time and I end up crashing. I was starting to wonder if the David Cameron level was mean to never end due to the paranoid delusion that the game was engineered to allow run cameron's car into ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• thus killing him.

Kinda sad to say this about a $3 game, but buy it on sale.

reviewText:
I just spent a bit of my time playing the single greatest game of all time.

And it was called GTA V. And then, I played this. Personally, I find this way funnier, in the way that a 22 minute television program can be way funnier than a 3 hour comedy film extravaganza. I'm glad I could pick this up before it got taken down from the store, because we all knew that was going to happen.

Soundtrack.

I want it. I want the soundtrack so badly to this so I can literally drive around in my car and listen to it full blast with the windows down. I'm not even being sarcastic here, I really find it to be this funny. Particularly the opera bits.

And now for something completely different.

Because as an American, I can't in good conscience review this game without throwing in a Monty Python reference. I do this both because I'm cultural ignorant and assume this is all that has happened in the UK since the year 785, and because it's obligatory.

A lot of people complain about this game being crappy. Yes, the game is crap. It's crap on purpose, which is the best kind of crap. This hits every part of my brain that makes me giggle and then it tickles those tender sensitive bits so that I can laugh harder. Hardy-har-har, it is to laugh.

If you didn't get this before it got removed from the store, it's your loss and you should be ashamed of yourself.

99/10.
